{% call components.section("Style") -%}
  <p>A default blockquote consists of three required elements, a quote icon, text, and attribution. It can be left- or center-aligned on large and small screens. A left-aligned blockquote can also feature additional elements, like large text styles and components on top or to the right whereas a center-aligned blockquote can't include anything else.</p>

  <div>
  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="centered">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/blockquote/blockquote-style-1.svg' | url }}" alt="blockquote breakdown" style="--example-img-max-width: 623px;">
    </div>
  {%- endcall %}
  <p class="footnote footnote-alignment" style="display:block;">Only the left-aligned blockquote can include these additional elements</p>
  </div>

  <h4>Theme</h4>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="centered">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/blockquote/blockquote-theme-1.svg' | url }}" alt="Example of a left-aligned blockquote" style="--example-img-max-width: 652px;">
    </div>
  {%- endcall %}

    {% call components.example(palette='darkest') %}
    <div class="centered">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/blockquote/blockquote-theme-2.svg' | url }}" alt="Example of a left-aligned blockquote" style="--example-img-max-width: 623px;">
    </div>
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Quote icon</h4>
  <p>A red quote icon is always placed above the blockquote text in both themes.</p>

  <h4>Attribution</h4>
  <p>A blockquote always has attribution text underneath that gives credit to whoever the quote is from.</p>

  <h4>Additional elements</h4>
  <p>A left-aligned blockquote can feature additional elements on top, like large text styles or a logo. If these optional elements are used, a thin vertical bar is added to the left of a blockquote to maintain focus with readers. These additional elements can be used without including a component to the right.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="centered">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/blockquote/blockquote-additional-elements-1.svg' | url }}" alt="Example of a left-aligned blockquote" style="--example-img-max-width: 632px;">
    </div>
  {%- endcall %}

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="centered">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/blockquote/blockquote-additional-elements-2.svg' | url }}" alt="Example of a left-aligned blockquote" style="--example-img-max-width: 632px;">
    </div>
  {%- endcall %}


{%- endcall %}


{% call components.section("Usage") -%}
  <h4>Layout</h4>
  <p>The width of a blockquote on large screens is determined by alignment and if they're used with a component. <!--For more information about layout configurations, see Layout (future link)--></p>

  <div class="centered margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    <img src="{{ '/assets/blockquote/blockquote-layout-1.svg' | url }}" alt="Blockquote layout" class="margin-bottom--2">
  </div>
  <p class="footnote">When used on its own or with large text styles or a logo on top, a left-aligned blockquote is seven grid columns wide</p>

  <div class="centered margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/blockquote/blockquote-layout-2.svg' | url }}" alt="Blockquote layout" class="margin-bottom--2">
    </div>
  <p class="footnote">A center-aligned blockquote is eight grid columns wide and can't be used with other components</p>

  <div class="centered margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/blockquote/blockquote-layout-3.svg' | url }}" alt="blockquote layout" class="margin-bottom--2">
    </div>
  <p class="footnote">When used with a <a href="../card">Card</a>, a left-aligned blockquote is seven grid columns wide (7-1-4 layout)</p>

  <div class="centered margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/blockquote/blockquote-layout-4.svg' | url }}" alt="Blockquote layout" class="margin-bottom--2">
    </div>
  <p class="footnote">When used with a <a href="../video-thumbnail">Video thumbnail</a>, a left-aligned blockquote is five grid columns (5-1-6 layout)</p>
{%- endcall %}

